ronelson wrote:Quote:But by all accounts the Knight of Flowers is highly skilled and not just in tourneys.It wasn't actually about him getting his ass kicked. It was about the Lannister's fighting Robb's forces, and here's an army twice as big as that army with a free approach to King's Landing, just sitting around in tourney to make their King feel good about himself.Yep. It's not that southerners are poor fighters so much as the people joining up with Renly were treating it as a game, stopping at every castle on the way to have picnics and hold tournaments. I think the comment also cuts at how poorly suited and ill-prepared they were for the upcoming war and winter. And it helped show how Catelyn had been molded into more of a Northerner than she originally appeared when compared to true Northerners early in the series...it's all about perspective.Ok, I saw Ep3 and I think the Margaery/Renly scene helps show, in way that wasn't obvious in the books, that she wants to be Queen. It may help put future events in clearer perspective (i.e. why she would even agree to marry Joffrey, then Tommen, then whoever else comes next...) and make her appear less a pawn used to simply join the Tyrells with whoever may be closest to the throne at the time...
