Barmaglot wrote:Bet you hated LotR too.I enjoyed it on the whole. Tolkien's vegetation fetish did get cumbersome at times. It too was long, but the whole thing was over and done with in 3 books, not 5 and counting.fitten wrote:Unfortunately, if all a reader thinks that has happened during that time is "they were traveling" then the reader is very likely skimming the book and/or not paying attention anyway.Shall I summarise the book for you by chapter or by character? Bear in mind, I'm only 40% done.Tyrion: travels first by palanquin, then by boat, then by horse, then by boat. Drinks and broods.Daenerys: fails at suppressing insurrection, raising dragons, being decisive. Wants sex but doesn't know how to get it.Jon: Recruits more men than he can feed. Politics with Stannis.Bran: Travels north, hides in cave. Regularly mind rapes Hodor.Davos: Gets caught. Gets released.Melisandre: Magic is hard.Quentyn Martell: Acquires aliases.Did I omit much?Look, I'm still reading the book. I've read all of them in quick succession. I like high fantasy and high magic settings more than the opposite. I'm not very fond of intrigue. So what I'm saying is I'm somewhat outside the target audience for the books but am still somewhat enjoying them.That doesn't change the fact they're plodding and prolix.
